Visualization: Case 2- Improve Retention in the Corporate Segment by Focusing on Medium-Risk Customers 6


Positive Insight:

The Corporate segment has a churn rate of 64%, with 128 churned customers, representing a larger churn volume compared to the Consumer segment. The GPM for the Corporate segment is 17.8%, which makes retention more cost-effective in this segment. By focusing on medium-risk customers, we can improve retention with lower investment due to higher customer profitability.



Negative Insight:

While the Corporate segment has a higher churn rate (64%) compared to the Consumer segment (63%), the 17.8% GPM indicates higher profitability per customer. This makes retention more profitable even though there are more churned customers. Focusing on medium-risk Corporate customers offers a higher financial impact from retention.


Case 2 ROI:
Focusing on medium-risk Corporate customers could result in $153,660.49 in potential savings annually, with an ROI of 120%. The larger churn volume in the Corporate segment makes this a valuable target, even with the lower ROI.
